Toronto CCNI data sources

1. Tree canopy coverage
City of Toronto Open Data / tree canopy study
Used to identify canopy deficit at tract level.

2. 2021 census socio-demographic variables
Statistics Canada / City of Toronto neighbourhood or tract-based census profile data
Variables used for vulnerability interpretation included income and racialized population share.

3. Building data / derived building density
City of Toronto building data
Used to derive a tract-level built-form proxy for heat amplification and hardscape intensity.

4. Final processed file
A processed spatial file was used to assemble the final tract-level CCNI workflow and map output.

